@danwang15, and we're very pumped to show our newest health tech product, Jonda ü•≥¬† ¬† Have all your health records in a single, secure, easy-to-use place with the Jonda app, that allows you to easily and securely scan or upload any of your medical documents using automated and intelligent systems.
The problem üòï: To date thousands of healthcare organisations each have their own IT platforms, standards, and privacy controls. Currently, not a single medical institution has a complete picture of any single patient. Patients therefore need to be their own case managers, especially those with moderate to severe chronic and rare diseases.¬†‚Ä®¬†
The solution ü§©: As a medical doctor and chronic disease sufferer that has experienced the challenges of health data fragmentation and system interoperabi‚Ä¶

You are given an m x n binary matrix grid. An island is a group of 1's (representing land) connected 4-directionally (horizontal or vertical.) You may assume all four edges of the grid are surrounded by water.
The area of an island is the number of cells with a value 1 in the island.
Return the maximum area of an island in grid. If there is no island, return 0.

class Solution:
    def maxAreaOfIsland(self, grid: List[List[int]]) -> int:
        ROWS, COLS = len(grid), len(grid[0])
        visit = set()

        def dfs(r, c):
            if (
                r < 0
                or r == ROWS
                or c < 0
                or c == COLS
                or grid[r][c] == 0
                or (r, c) in visit
            ):
                return 0

            visit.add((r, c))
            return 1 + dfs(r + 1, c) + dfs(r - 1, c) + dfs(r, c + 1) + dfs(r, c - 1)


        area = 0

        for r in range(ROWS):
            for c in range(COLS):
                area = max(area, dfs(r, c))

        return area
